This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object recognition in the presence of background noise and distractors. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of mid-level feature selectivity in visual area V4 and Inferotemporal cortex (IT), which are key areas in the visual processing pathway. 

The paper also mentions the use of deep networks such as convolutional neural networks and deep belief networks, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). 

The paper's focus on addressing the problem of object recognition suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The paper's use of prior knowledge built into cortical circuits suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper's mention of flexible communication between different layers of representation suggests that it may also belong to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
